  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/quota/evaluator/core/pods.go#L50\n\nThe scenario that presented a problem was the following:\n\na) create pods in a namespace that do not make a memory claim\nb) add a quota that tracks memory\nc) update one of the pods previously created by reducing its active deadline.\n\nExpected result:\nSince a pod cannot change its resources via update, we should have been allowed to update the pod spec.\n\nActual Result:\nerror since the pod did not make a memory claim, quota rejects the pod.\n",
